main event: Pilots sighted a large cigar-shaped object flying southeast over Panay Island, Philippines on October 4, 1960.
interesting points: The object was described as cigar-shaped and flying at an unknown altitude.
The object was sighted from a distance of approximately 1.5 miles.
The pilots were able to observe and time the object's flight for an unspecified duration.
The report mentions a previous sighting of an oil plain bearing 139 degrees from the pilots' location.
The report suggests the pilots were considered reliable and rational observers.
